{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1028,"text":"As you've probably noticed,"},{"time":2755,"text":"in recent years, a lot\nof western forests have burned"},{"time":5956,"text":"in large and destructive wildfires."},{"time":10840,"text":"If you're like me --"},{"time":12087,"text":"this western landscape\nis actually why my family and I live here."},{"time":17558,"text":"And as a scientist and a father,"},{"time":19872,"text":"I've become deeply concerned\nabout what we're leaving behind"},{"time":23967,"text":"for our kids, and now my five grandkids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28756,"text":"In the US, an area that's larger\nthan the state of Oregon has burned"},{"time":33653,"text":"in just the last 10 years,"},{"time":36342,"text":"and tens of thousands of homes\nhave been destroyed."},{"time":41098,"text":"Acres burned and homes destroyed\nhave steadily increased"},{"time":45886,"text":"over the last three decades,"},{"time":50328,"text":"and individual fires that are bigger\nthan 100,000 acres --"},{"time":55808,"text":"they're actually on the rise."},{"time":57460,"text":"These are what we call \"megafires.\""},{"time":61229,"text":"Megafires are the result of the way\nwe've managed this western landscape"},{"time":66023,"text":"over the last 150 years"},{"time":68663,"text":"in a steadily warming climate."},{"time":71890,"text":"Much of the destruction\nthat we are currently seeing"},{"time":75600,"text":"could actually have been avoided."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78616,"text":"I've spent my entire career\nstudying these western landscapes,"},{"time":82162,"text":"and the science is pretty clear:"},{"time":84911,"text":"if we don't change a few\nof our fire-management habits,"},{"time":89996,"text":"we're going to lose many more\nof our beloved forests."},{"time":94062,"text":"Some won't recover in our lifetime"},{"time":97411,"text":"or my kids' lifetime."},{"time":99603,"text":"It's time we confront\nsome tough truths about wildfires,"},{"time":104006,"text":"and come to understand that we need\nto learn to better live with them"},{"time":109162,"text":"and change how they come to our forests,"},{"time":112829,"text":"our homes"},{"time":115047,"text":"and our communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117654,"text":"So why is this happening?"},{"time":119508,"text":"Well, that's what I want\nto talk to you about today."},{"time":124180,"text":"You see this forest?"},{"time":128536,"text":"Isn't it beautiful?"},{"time":137877,"text":"Well, the forests that we see today"},{"time":141108,"text":"look nothing like the forests\nof 100 or 150 years ago."},{"time":147318,"text":"Thankfully, panoramic photos\nwere taken in the 1930s"},{"time":151005,"text":"from thousands of western\nmountaintop lookouts,"},{"time":154917,"text":"and they show a fair approximation"},{"time":157380,"text":"of the forest that we inherited."},{"time":160441,"text":"The best word to describe\nthese forests of old is \"patchy.\""},{"time":165303,"text":"The historical forest landscape\nwas this constantly evolving patchwork"},{"time":169325,"text":"of open and closed\ncanopy forests of all ages,"},{"time":173108,"text":"and there was so much evidence of fire."},{"time":177759,"text":"And most fires were pretty small\nby today's standards."},{"time":182070,"text":"And it's important to understand\nthat this landscape was open,"},{"time":186102,"text":"with meadows and open canopy forests,"},{"time":188648,"text":"and it was the grasses of the meadows"},{"time":190948,"text":"and in the grassy understories\nof the open forest"},{"time":194444,"text":"that many of the wildfires were carried."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199797,"text":"There were other forces at work, too,\nshaping this historical patchwork:"},{"time":203883,"text":"for example, topography,\nwhether a place faces north or south"},{"time":207727,"text":"or it's on a ridge top\nor in a valley bottom;"},{"time":210449,"text":"elevation, how far up the mountain it is;"},{"time":213318,"text":"and weather, whether a place\ngets a lot of snow and rain,"},{"time":217938,"text":"sunlight and warmth."},{"time":220010,"text":"These things all worked together"},{"time":223103,"text":"to shape the way the forest grew."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225974,"text":"And the way the forest grew\nshaped the way fire behaved"},{"time":231163,"text":"on the landscape."},{"time":233431,"text":"There was crosstalk\nbetween the patterns and the processes."},{"time":238704,"text":"You can see the new dry forest."},{"time":240625,"text":"Trees were open grown\nand fairly far apart."},{"time":243851,"text":"Fires were frequent here,\nand when they occurred,"},{"time":246320,"text":"they weren't that severe,"},{"time":247922,"text":"while further up the mountain,"},{"time":249376,"text":"in the moist and the cold forests,"},{"time":251523,"text":"trees were more densely grown\nand fires were less frequent,"},{"time":254785,"text":"but when they occurred,\nthey were quite a bit more severe."},{"time":258127,"text":"These different forest types,\nthe environments that they grew in"},{"time":261794,"text":"and fire severity --\nthey all worked together"},{"time":264881,"text":"to shape this historical patchwork."},{"time":268429,"text":"And there was so much power"},{"time":271837,"text":"in this patchwork."},{"time":273904,"text":"It provided a natural mechanism"},{"time":276455,"text":"to resist the spread of future fires\nacross the landscape."},{"time":281002,"text":"Once a patch of forest burned,"},{"time":283172,"text":"it helped to prevent the flow\nof fire across the landscape."},{"time":287046,"text":"A way to think about it is,"},{"time":288561,"text":"the burned patches\nhelped the rest of the forest"},{"time":293148,"text":"to be forest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296677,"text":"Let's add humans to the mix."},{"time":299144,"text":"For 10,000 years, Native Americans\nlived on this landscape,"},{"time":302893,"text":"and they intentionally burned it -- a lot."},{"time":307284,"text":"They used fire to burn meadows\nand to thin certain forests"},{"time":311200,"text":"so they could grow more food."},{"time":313269,"text":"They used fire to increase graze"},{"time":316298,"text":"for the deer and the elk\nand the bison that they hunted."},{"time":320158,"text":"And most importantly, they figured out"},{"time":322695,"text":"if they burned in the spring and the fall,"},{"time":325345,"text":"they could avoid the out-of-control\nfires of summer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329508,"text":"European settlement -- it occurred\nmuch later, in the mid-1800s,"},{"time":334016,"text":"and by the 1880s, livestock\ngrazing was in high gear."},{"time":338315,"text":"I mean, if you think about it,\nthe cattle and the sheep ate the grasses"},{"time":342120,"text":"which had been the conveyer belt\nfor the historical fires,"},{"time":346185,"text":"and this prevented once-frequent fires\nfrom thinning out trees"},{"time":350303,"text":"and burning up dead wood."},{"time":352634,"text":"Later came roads and railroads,\nand they acted as potent firebreaks,"},{"time":357737,"text":"interrupting further the flow of fire\nacross this landscape."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361733,"text":"And then something happened\nwhich caused a sudden pivot"},{"time":365617,"text":"in our society."},{"time":367489,"text":"In 1910, we had a huge wildfire."},{"time":371586,"text":"It was the size\nof the state of Connecticut."},{"time":375275,"text":"We called it \"the Big Burn.\""},{"time":377939,"text":"It stretched from eastern Washington\nto western Montana,"},{"time":381912,"text":"and it burned, in a few days,\nthree million acres,"},{"time":385619,"text":"devoured several towns,\nand it killed 87 people."},{"time":390104,"text":"Most of them were firefighters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393178,"text":"Because of the Big Burn, wildfire\nbecame public enemy number one,"},{"time":397185,"text":"and this would shape the way\nthat we would think about wildfire"},{"time":400630,"text":"in our society"},{"time":401935,"text":"for the next hundred years."},{"time":404880,"text":"Thereafter, the Forest Service,\njust five years young at the time,"},{"time":408335,"text":"was tasked with the responsibility\nof putting out all wildfires"},{"time":413491,"text":"on 193 million acres of public lands,"},{"time":417057,"text":"and they took this responsibility"},{"time":419021,"text":"very seriously."},{"time":420872,"text":"They developed this unequaled\nability to put fires out,"},{"time":424846,"text":"and they put out 95 to 98 percent"},{"time":428122,"text":"of all fires every single year in the US."},{"time":433120,"text":"And from this point on,\nit was now fire suppression"},{"time":437387,"text":"and not wildfires"},{"time":438941,"text":"that would become a prime\nshaper of our forests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443943,"text":"After World War II, timber harvesting\ngot going in the west,"},{"time":447467,"text":"and the logging removed\nthe large and the old trees."},{"time":450614,"text":"These were survivors\nof centuries of wildfires."},{"time":455919,"text":"And the forest filled in."},{"time":457875,"text":"Thin-barked, fire-sensitive\nsmall trees filled in the gaps,"},{"time":462820,"text":"and our forests became dense,\nwith trees so layered and close together"},{"time":468790,"text":"that they were touching each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471357,"text":"So fires were unintentionally blocked\nby roads and railroads,"},{"time":475299,"text":"the cattle and sheep ate the grass,"},{"time":477758,"text":"then along comes fire suppression\nand logging, removing the big trees,"},{"time":482102,"text":"and you know what happened?"},{"time":483451,"text":"All these factors worked together"},{"time":485729,"text":"to allow the forest to fill in,"},{"time":488638,"text":"creating what I call\nthe current epidemic of trees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493163,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":496678,"text":"Go figure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497878,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":498949,"text":"More trees than the landscape can support."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503506,"text":"So when you compare what forests\nlooked like 100 years ago and today,"},{"time":508290,"text":"the change is actually remarkable."},{"time":510800,"text":"Notice how the patchwork has filled in."},{"time":513234,"text":"Dry south slopes --"},{"time":514806,"text":"they're now covered with trees."},{"time":517843,"text":"A patchwork that was once\nsculptured by mostly small"},{"time":520846,"text":"and sort of medium-sized fires"},{"time":522628,"text":"has filled in."},{"time":524145,"text":"Do you see the blanket of trees?"},{"time":526679,"text":"After just 150 years,"},{"time":528974,"text":"we have a dense carpet of forest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531555,"text":"But there's more."},{"time":533312,"text":"Because trees are growing\nso close together,"},{"time":536291,"text":"and because tree species,\ntree sizes and ages"},{"time":539643,"text":"are so similar across large areas,"},{"time":543314,"text":"fires not only move easily\nfrom acre to acre,"},{"time":546365,"text":"but now, so do diseases\nand insect outbreaks,"},{"time":551896,"text":"which are killing or reducing the vitality"},{"time":555248,"text":"of really large sections of forest now."},{"time":558488,"text":"And after a century without fire,"},{"time":561371,"text":"dead branches and downed trees\non the forest floor,"},{"time":564974,"text":"they're at powder-keg levels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567956,"text":"What's more, our summers\nare getting hotter"},{"time":570605,"text":"and they're getting drier"},{"time":572784,"text":"and they're getting windier."},{"time":575163,"text":"And the fire season is now\n40 to 80 days longer each year."},{"time":581168,"text":"Because of this,\nclimatologists are predicting"},{"time":583692,"text":"that the area burned since 2000"},{"time":586936,"text":"will double or triple"},{"time":589745,"text":"in the next three decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593015,"text":"And we're building houses\nin the middle of this."},{"time":596413,"text":"Two recently published studies tell us"},{"time":598546,"text":"that more than 60 percent\nof all new housing starts are being built"},{"time":603107,"text":"in this flammable and dangerous mess."},{"time":607145,"text":"So when we do get a fire,"},{"time":609722,"text":"large areas can literally go up in smoke."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616363,"text":"How do you feel now"},{"time":619580,"text":"about the forest image"},{"time":622070,"text":"that I first showed you?"},{"time":623773,"text":"It scares the heck out of me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627729,"text":"So what do we do?"},{"time":630010,"text":"We need to restore\nthe power of the patchwork."},{"time":633544,"text":"We need to put the right kind of fire"},{"time":636717,"text":"back into the system again."},{"time":638643,"text":"It's how we can resize\nthe severity of many of our future fires."},{"time":645277,"text":"And the silver lining is\nthat we have tools"},{"time":647770,"text":"and we have know-how to do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650268,"text":"Let's look at some of the tools."},{"time":652431,"text":"We can use prescribed burning\nto intentionally thin out trees"},{"time":657222,"text":"and burn up dead fuels."},{"time":659740,"text":"We do this to systematically\nreduce them and keep them reduced."},{"time":664785,"text":"And what is that going to do?"},{"time":666191,"text":"It's going to create already-burned\npatches on the landscape"},{"time":669089,"text":"that will resist the flow of future fires."},{"time":672389,"text":"We can combine mechanical thinning\nwith some of these treatments"},{"time":675725,"text":"where it's appropriate to do so,"},{"time":677440,"text":"and capture some commercial value"},{"time":679238,"text":"and perhaps underwrite\nsome of these treatments,"},{"time":682193,"text":"especially around urban areas."},{"time":684766,"text":"And the best news of all\nis that prescribed burning produces"},{"time":688021,"text":"so much less smoke than wildfires do."},{"time":691701,"text":"It's not even close."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693074,"text":"But there's a hitch:"},{"time":694962,"text":"prescribed burning smoke is currently\nregulated under air quality rules"},{"time":699975,"text":"as an avoidable nuisance."},{"time":702557,"text":"But wildfire smoke?"},{"time":704262,"text":"It simply gets a pass."},{"time":708153,"text":"Makes sense, doesn't it? (Laughs)"},{"time":710742,"text":"So you know what happens?"},{"time":712041,"text":"We do far too little prescribed burning,"},{"time":715312,"text":"and we continually eat smoke\nin the summers"},{"time":719147,"text":"from megafires."},{"time":720572,"text":"We all need to work together\nto get this changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724711,"text":"And finally, there's managed wildfires."},{"time":726696,"text":"Instead of putting all the fires out,"},{"time":729903,"text":"we need to put some of them back to work"},{"time":732456,"text":"thinning forests and reducing dead fuels."},{"time":736005,"text":"We can herd them around the landscape"},{"time":738696,"text":"when it's appropriate to do so"},{"time":740633,"text":"to help restore the power\nof the patchwork."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746623,"text":"And as you've probably figured out by now,"},{"time":750386,"text":"this is actually a social problem."},{"time":752616,"text":"It's got ecological\nand climate explanations,"},{"time":755623,"text":"but it's a social problem,\nand it will take us humans to solve it."},{"time":761026,"text":"Public support for these tools is poor."},{"time":763482,"text":"Prescribed burning and managed wildfires\nare not well-supported."},{"time":767188,"text":"We actually all simply want fires\nto magically go away"},{"time":772455,"text":"and take that pesky smoke\nwith them, don't we?"},{"time":777122,"text":"But there is no future\nwithout lots of fire and lots of smoke."},{"time":782174,"text":"That option is actually not on the table."},{"time":787038,"text":"Until we, the owners of public lands,\nmake it our high priority"},{"time":792243,"text":"to do something about\nthe current situation,"},{"time":796002,"text":"we're going to experience\ncontinued losses to megafires."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799647,"text":"So it's up to us."},{"time":801569,"text":"We can spread this message\nto our lawmakers,"},{"time":804312,"text":"folks who can help us manage our fires"},{"time":808265,"text":"and our forests."},{"time":813680,"text":"If we're unsuccessful,"},{"time":817190,"text":"where will you go to play"},{"time":820140,"text":"when your favorite places\nare burned black?"},{"time":825096,"text":"Where will you go"},{"time":827298,"text":"to breathe deep"},{"time":830052,"text":"and slow?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":832080,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833278,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}